 \"useEffect\" is called conditionally. React Hooks must be called in the exact same order in every component render. Did you accidentally call a React Hook after an early return?",["2063"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'fetchOptions'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2064"],["2065"],"@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars","'_value' is defined but never used.","unusedVar",["2066"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'onUpdateModel'. Either include it or remove the dependency array. If 'onUpdateModel' changes too often, find the parent component that defines it and wrap that definition in useCallback.",["2067"],["2068"],["2069"],["2070"],"react-hooks/set-state-in-effect","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/home/loza/Work/cobros-web-react-ts/src/components/Custom/Input/FileSelector.tsx:49:7\n  47 |     if (disabled) {\n  48 |       // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/set-state-in-effect\n> 49 |       setIsDisabled(true)\n     |       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  50 |     } else if (maxFiles && initialFiles.length > maxFiles - 1) {\n  51 |       setIsDisabled(true)\n  52 |     } else {",["2071"],"React Hook useMemo has a missing dependency: 'messageTypeMap'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2072"],["2073"],["2074"],["2075"],"React Hook useEffect has missing dependencies: 'getModelValue', 'handleSelectOption', 'options', and 'selectFirstOption'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2076"],["2077"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'getOptions'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2078"],["2079"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'handleSelectOption'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2080"],["2081"],"React Hook useEffect has missing dependencies: 'getModelValue' and 'itemKey'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2082"],["2083"],"Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/home/loza/Work/cobros-web-react-ts/src/components/Custom/SelectV2.tsx:86:7\n  84 |     if (select_first_item && items.length > 0) {\n  85 |       // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/set-state-in-effect\n> 86 |       handleItem(items[0])\n     |       ^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  87 |     } else if (value) {\n  88 |       const selectedItem = items.find((item) => item[field_value] === value)\n  89 |       if (selectedItem) {",["2084"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'requestOptions?.filters'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2085"],["2086"],"React Hook useEffect has a complex expression in the dependency array. Extract it to a separate variable so it can be statically checked.","CallExpression",["2087"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'setFirstOption'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2088"],["2089"],"React Hook useEffect has missing dependencies: 'fetchOptions' and 'inputValue'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2090"],["2091"],"React Hook useMemo has a missing dependency: 'fetchOptions'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2092"],["2093"],"React Hook useMemo has a complex expression in the dependency array. Extract it to a separate variable so it can be statically checked.",["2094"],["2095"],"React Hook useMemo has missing dependencies: 'api', 'fieldsForms', 'modalCustom', 'onBeforeDelete', 'onBeforeSave', 'onUpdateModel', 'useModalDeleteLogic', 'useModalEdit', and 'widthModal'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2096"],["2097"],["2098"],["2099"],"React Hook useMemo has a missing dependency: 'alwaysVisible'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2100"],["2101"],"React Hook useMemo has missing dependencies: 'buildFilter' and 'hasFilterConfig'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2102"],["2103"],"React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'fetchCustomer'. Either include it or remove the dependency array.",["2104"],["2105"],"Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/home/loza/Work/cobros-web-react-ts/src/views/admin/colas/management/components/StepPromises.tsx:50:7\n  48 |\n  49 |       // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/set-state-in-effect\n> 50 |       setPromises(mapped)\n     |       ^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  51 |     }\n  52 |   }, [promisesData])\n  53 |",["2106"],"react-refresh/only-export-components","Fast refresh only works when a file only exports components. Use a new file to share constants or functions between components.","namedExport",["2107"],["2108"],{"desc":"2109","fix":"2110"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2113","fix":"2114"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2115","fix":"2116"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2115","fix":"2117"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2118","fix":"2119"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2120","fix":"2121"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2122","fix":"2123"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2124","fix":"2125"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2120","fix":"2126"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2127","fix":"2128"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2127","fix":"2129"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2130","fix":"2131"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2132","fix":"2133"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2134","fix":"2135"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2136","fix":"2137"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"desc":"2138","fix":"2139"},{"kind":"2111","justification":"2112"},{"kind":"2111","justification